This paper deals with natural language processing techniques such as summarization and text-to-speech conversion, which are commonly studied in the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). It also involves the use of algorithms and modules for text analysis and processing, which falls under the sub-category of software development (cs.SD). The paper also deals with information retrieval techniques for summarization, which is a common topic in the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR). The system is designed to aid visually impaired people, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and assistive technologies (cs.SI).
